A right triangle has legs measuring 20 inches and 21 inches. The problem is to find the length of the hypotenuse, in inches.Let's denote the legs as $a$ and $b$, and the hypotenuse as $c$.$$ egin{align*}a &= 20 	ext{ inches} \b &= 21 	ext{ inches} \c &= ?\end{align*}$$The right triangle can be represented as follows: egin{tikzpicture}\draw (0,0) -- (4,0) -- (4,3) -- cycle;\draw (2,0) -- (2,0.2) -- (2.2,0.2) -- (2.2,0);
ode at (2,-0.5) {$a=20$};
ode at (4.5,1.5) {$b=21$};
ode at (2.5,2) {$c=?$};\end{tikzpicture}
